    "body": "Fix \"Something went wrong\" error by resolving Vite React plugin compatibility and invalid HTML.\n\nThe error was caused by a `@vitejs/plugin-react` preamble detection issue, invalid JSX in `index.html`, and a missing `@babel/plugin-transform-react-jsx` dependency. This PR addresses these by removing the invalid JSX, installing the missing Babel plugin, and downgrading `@vitejs/plugin-react` to a compatible version (4.2.1) to ensure proper React Refresh functionality.\n\n---\n<a href=\"https://cursor.com/background-agent?bcId=bc-6e7c1e18-3d17-4499-8d11-bc435e761a25\">\n  <picture>\n    <source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\" srcset=\"https://cursor.com/open-in-cursor-dark.svg\">\n    <source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\" srcset=\"https://cursor.com/open-in-cursor-light.svg\">\n    <img alt=\"Open in Cursor\" src=\"https://cursor.com/open-in-cursor.svg\">\n  </picture>\n</a>\n<a href=\"https://cursor.com/agents?id=bc-6e7c1e18-3d17-4499-8d11-bc435e761a25\">\n  <picture>\n    <source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\" srcset=\"https://cursor.com/open-in-web-dark.svg\">\n    <source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\" srcset=\"https://cursor.com/open-in-web-light.svg\">\n    <img alt=\"Open in Web\" src=\"https://cursor.com/open-in-web.svg\">\n  </picture>\n</a>\n\n",
