    "body": "Update Netlify build command to use Yarn instead of npm to resolve dependency installation failures.\n\nThe build was failing because `netlify.toml` specified `npm` commands, but Netlify was actually using `yarn install`. This mismatch caused the `husky install` script to fail with a \"husky: not found\" error during the Yarn installation process. This change aligns the build command with Yarn.\n\n---\n<a href=\"https://cursor.com/background-agent?bcId=bc-f6fb8b55-8d9a-4a05-8f1f-c21aa403df74\">\n  <picture>\n    <source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\" srcset=\"https://cursor.com/open-in-cursor-dark.svg\">\n    <source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\" srcset=\"https://cursor.com/open-in-cursor-light.svg\">\n    <img alt=\"Open in Cursor\" src=\"https://cursor.com/open-in-cursor.svg\">\n  </picture>\n</a>\n<a href=\"https://cursor.com/agents?id=bc-f6fb8b55-8d9a-4a05-8f1f-c21aa403df74\">\n  <picture>\n    <source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\" srcset=\"https://cursor.com/open-in-web-dark.svg\">\n    <source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\" srcset=\"https://cursor.com/open-in-web-light.svg\">\n    <img alt=\"Open in Web\" src=\"https://cursor.com/open-in-web.svg\">\n  </picture>\n</a>\n\n",
